  - q: "What types of tile do you install?"
    a: "We install ceramic tile, porcelain tile, natural stone (marble, travertine, slate), mosaic tiles, and large-format tiles. Ake has experience with all tile sizes and patterns, from simple straight-lay to complex herringbone and diagonal patterns."
  - q: "How long does tile flooring last?"
    a: "Tile is one of the most durable flooring options available. Properly installed ceramic and porcelain tile can last 50+ years with basic maintenance. Natural stone can last even longer. The key is proper installation and grouting — which is exactly what Ake specializes in."
  - q: "Can you install heated floors under tile?"
    a: "Yes. Radiant floor heating works exceptionally well under tile, which conducts and retains heat efficiently. Ake can install tile over electric radiant heat mats for a warm, comfortable bathroom or kitchen floor. This is especially popular in Oregon's cool, damp climate."
  - q: "How do I maintain tile floors?"
    a: "Tile floors are low-maintenance. Sweep regularly and mop with a pH-neutral cleaner. The grout is the part that needs the most attention — we recommend sealing grout lines every 1-2 years to prevent staining and moisture penetration."
