<h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);font-weight:600;color:var(--text-primary);margin-top:var(--space-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">What Affects Tile Installation Cost?</h3>
<p style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Every tile project is different. Here are the main factors that affect your investment:</p>
<ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:2;padding-left:var(--space-lg);">
  <li><strong>Tile material</strong> — Ceramic is the most affordable; natural stone is premium</li>
  <li><strong>Pattern complexity</strong> — Straight-lay costs less than herringbone or diagonal layouts</li>
  <li><strong>Subfloor condition</strong> — Leveling or repair adds to the project scope</li>
  <li><strong>Room size</strong> — Larger areas have a lower per-square-foot cost</li>
  <li><strong>Waterproofing</strong> — Showers and wet areas require membrane work</li>
</ul>
